sentences: Slim Willet (Winston Lee Moore, December 1, 1919, Dublin, Texas â€“ July 1, 1966) was an American disc jockey, musician, and songwriter.
Taking the stage name Slim Willet, he released his debut single in 1950 with "Tool Pusher from Snyder".

He released several hit singles during this time, among them "Red Rose", "No Love Song to You", and "Don't Let the Stars Get in Your Eyes", which became a major hit for both Perry Como and Skeets McDonald in 1952.
